tableData.tdHtmlString: Nepalese royal massacre
tableData.text: Nepalese royal massacre

tableData.tdHtmlString: On June 1, 2001, Crown Prince Dipendra Bir Bikram Shah killed 9 people and injured 5 others at a house in the grounds of the Narayanhity Royal Palace, before shooting himself and dying three days later on June 4, 2001.

tableData.text: "Hostage Rescue in Lima"

tableData.tdHtmlString: Japanese embassy hostage crisis
tableData.text: Japanese embassy hostage crisis

tableData.tdHtmlString: On April 22, 1997, hundreds of high-level diplomats, government and military officials and business executives were freed from the grasp of 14 members of the Túpac Amaru Revolutionary Movement (MRTA) during a raid on the Japanese embassy in Lima by Peruvian Armed Forces commandos, during which one hostage, two commandos, and all the MRTA militants died.

"The North Hollywood Shootout"
tableData.text: "The North Hollywood Shootout"

tableData.tdHtmlString: North Hollywood shootout
tableData.text: North Hollywood shootout

tableData.tdHtmlString: On February 28, 1997, two heavily armed bank robbers, Larry Eugene Phillips Jr. and Emil Dechebal Matasareanu, engaged over 300 LAPD officers in a shootout in North Hollywood, Los Angeles. Both robbers were killed, eleven police officers and seven civilians were injured, and numerous vehicles and other property were damaged or destroyed by the nearly 2,000 rounds of ammunition fired by the robbers and the police.

tableData.text: "Shoot-Out in Marseilles"

tableData.tdHtmlString: Air France Flight 8969
tableData.text: Air France Flight 8969

tableData.tdHtmlString: On December 26, 1994, members of the Armed Islamic Group (GIA) hijacked Air France Flight 8969 in an attempt to destroy the Eiffel Tower. When the aircraft reached Marseille, the GIGN, an intervention group of the French Gendarmerie, stormed the plane and killed all four hijackers. 3 passengers were killed and 25 others were wounded.
